options.prompt:
[feature-thirtyeight-context-catalog]

Project: Script Kit GPUI, a Rust/GPUI desktop app with a standalone TypeScript/Vite/XState Feature Explorer in feature_explorer/. This repo uses lat.md as an architecture knowledge graph. For this repo, implementation/review work must keep lat.md updated when functionality, architecture, tests, or behavior change, and must run lat check. The canonical Codex skills are under .agents/skills/; legacy .claude/skills are migration material.

Goal: Help the local agent author Feature 038 (Agent Skills and AI Context Catalog) as a rich, hand-authored XState representation in feature_explorer/src/state/authoredFeatureMachines.ts. Features 001-037 already have authored machines. Feature 038 should model the live product contracts precisely enough for the Feature Explorer to distinguish skill catalog discovery/search, compact skill staging, typed AiContextPart variants, MCP kit://context resources/schema, context preview, attachment portal return, focused-target handoff, SDK aiStartChat ordered parts, and submit-time ContextResolutionReceipt outcomes.

Current evidence: The bundle includes AGENTS/CLAUDE process context, repo-local skill docs for mcp-context-resources/acp-context-composer/acp-chat-core/sdk-script-execution/protocol-automation/testing-quality-gates/lat-md, relevant lat.md pages including lat.md/verification.md and lat.md/feature-explorer.md, the Feature 038 chapter and prior raw Oracle answer, current authoredFeatureMachines excerpts, source owners, and focused tests. The local agent will edit locally after your response.

Deliverable: Return an implementation-ready authoring plan for Feature 038's authored machine. Please provide:
1. the key parallel/orthogonal regions or state clusters this machine should preserve;
2. the most important state names and transitions/events to encode;
3. regression/gap states that must stay visible so the explorer does not overclaim support;
4. metadata/wireframe/receipt fields worth putting into state meta so the UI remains auditable;
5. the focused verification commands to run after implementation;
6. any cautions where the feature overlaps existing Feature 003/004/030/032 machines but should remain distinct.

Repo-specific constraints: Mention the lat.md update rule and required lat check. Return your answer as text in this response only. Do not create, attach, export, or offer any downloadable file. Do not create local project artifacts yourself. The local agent will write any needed files, plans, notes, goals, commits, or verification logs using local tools.
